  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening the Linkages Between the Formal Justice System and the Traditional Dispute Resolution System to Improve Access to Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Traditional Dispute Resolution (TDR) Unit within the Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs; Indirect beneficiaries: Somali citizens, particularly vulnerable groups such as women, marginalized groups and children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to strengthen the linkages between the formal justice system and the traditional dispute resolution (TDR) system in Somalia, with the ultimate goal of supporting the Government of Somalia to improve access to justice, particularly for vulnerable groups, women and children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To promote the establishment of a stable and efficient judicial system in Somalia.</narrative>
  </description>
